[This fuller version confirms that typical cutaneous lesions had been noted in the team that slaughtered, butchered, and buried the index carcass. And that a total of 4 animals had died -- ample opportunity for human and canine cases.

Bomet is in the Rift Valley province, where we have been seeing livestock and wildlife outbreaks. For a map of Kenya, see http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/kenya_pol88.jpg. Bomet is in the very middle of Rift Valley Province: see at http://www.fallingrain.com/world/KE/08/Bomet.html. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED map of Bomet, Rift Valley, Kenya is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6949774,17486.]
